description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you a Registered Nurse looking for a new challenge?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for an experienced Registered Nurse to deliver the highest quality care to a baby girl based in Preston.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to her condition, our service user&#39;s clinical support team are required to administer advanced basic life support on a daily basis, which involves complex airway manoeuvres. This requires an individual who can be responsive and attentive in this fast paced and intense environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;She requires suctioning and has her nutrition, medication, and hydration via an NG tube she has several seizures a day which will require close monitoring.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who can demonstrate experience working in an intense clinical role and play a crucial part in their patients’ quality of life. This little girl needs a team who can care and nurture her around all her clinical requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Having lots of cuddles and nursery rhymes are part of her daily life, to keep her content and happy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a 2:1 care package where you will be assisted by an experienced Healthcare Assistant each shift.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work hard to build close relationships with our service users and their families as we understand the importance that we play in their lives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal applicant will hold a valid NMC PIN and have experience in either children&#39;s or adults nursing and can evidence hands-on clinical care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential Experience Required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Current NMC PIN &lt;br /&gt;* Advanced Life Support&lt;br /&gt;* Nasogastric Tube&lt;br /&gt;* Seizure Management &lt;br /&gt;* Oral Suctioning&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have the following shifts available;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Day shifts available from 8am - 8pm&lt;br /&gt;* Night shifts available from 8pm - 8am&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;The role we have will enable you to make a positive impact using your valuable skills and experience. You will also gain job satisfaction from the positive effects of your hands-on care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Why work for Apollo Home Healthcare?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We specialise in the provision of highly complex clinical care services delivered in the homes of service users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are passionate about delivering the highest standard of care and we recognise that our Nurses, Healthcare Assistants and Support Workers are integral to doing this. In return for your hard work and dedication you will receive:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible hours to suit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confirmed rotas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent rates of pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Holiday pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full clinical training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to work with other service users in the area&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ongoing professional training and development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need key workers on the front line supporting our service users in the fight against the COVID-19 Pandemic.&lt;/p&gt;
